1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new chapter to title 19 of the North Dakota Century
2 Code, relating to the creation of a safe food donation program.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. A new chapter to title 19 of the North Dakota Century Code is created and
5 enacted as follows:
6 Safe food donation program - Program participation requirements .
7 1. The department shall promote a safe food donation program.
8 2. To donate food under the program, an entity must be licensed under section 23 - 09 - 16 .
9 3. A charitable organization is not required to have a commercial kitchen or to be certified
10 by the department to receive food.
11 4. A charitable organization shall comply with food handling standards set by a local
12 public health unit.
13 5. A local public health unit shall:
14 a. Inspect licensed entities participating in the program;
15 b. Verify certification of an individual handling food on behalf of a charitable
16 organization; and
17 c. Establish safety guidelines and regulate the program.
18 Protection and liability.
19 1. A donor operating under this chapter is protected under subsection 2 of section
20 32 - 03.1 - 02.2, provided the donor is in compliance with established safety guidelines .
21 2. A charitable organization receiving food shall comply with safety guidelines
22 established by a local public health unit to protect a recipient's health.
23 Implementation - Oversight - Funding .
24 1. The department shall establish:
